@database "Volume"
@NODE Main "Volume"
					Volume 1.00 By Ronchi Francesco
						Copyright 1996

Volume is a simple program to change the volume of your Amiga's audio output.

		@{" About this tiny program " link AboutWin }

		@{" The Main Window         " link MainWin }
		@{" Interrupt Settings      " link InterWin }
		@{" Menu                    " link Menu }

		@{" Warnings...             " link WarnWin }

@ENDNODE

@NODE MainWin "Volume"
This is the main window. It shows a control (Knob) and a Levelmeter.
The first could be used to change the volume, ehile the second shows the current
volume level.
When Interrupts and Hit the Hardware are disabled, the volume could take some time to
change, since it is updated only every time the application execute an IO operation on the
audio.device.
		@{" Volume " link Volume }
		@{" Levelmeter " link Meter }
@ENDNODE

@NODE Volume "Volume"
This slider is used to change the volume.
@ENDNODE

@NODE Meter "Levelmeter"
This Levelmeter displays the current volume setting.
@ENDNODE

